# Code Style Guidelines

## Rule: Private Methods Placement

All newly added private methods and private helper classes/types must be placed at the end of the file, after all public and internal methods/types.

- Private methods should be grouped together at the end of the class/file
- Private helper classes/types should also be placed at the end
- This improves readability by keeping the public API visible at the top
- Only applies to newly added private methods/types
- Applies to all languages that support private methods/types (Kotlin, Scala, Java, Python, TypeScript, etc.)

Example (Kotlin):
```kotlin
// ✅ Good: Public methods first, private methods and helper classes at the end
class EmployeeService {
    fun getEmployee(id: String): Employee {
        return validateAndFetch(id)
    }
    
    fun updateEmployee(employee: Employee): Employee {
        return validateAndSave(employee)
    }
    
    private fun validateAndFetch(id: String): Employee {
        // private implementation
    }
    
    private fun validateAndSave(employee: Employee): Employee {
        // private implementation
    }
    
    private data class ValidationResult(val isValid: Boolean, val error: String?)
    
    private class EmployeeCache {
        // helper class implementation
    }
}
```

